,"colour":"ffe91e63","boundingBox":{"north":2,"south":-1,"east":129,"west":125.5},"placeCount":12,"restaurantCount":15,"bestTimeToVisit":"Best visited from September to April during the dry season.","heroImage":{"index":0,"assetPath":"","isLocal":false,"url":"https://images.unsplash.com/photo-1704797390682-76479a29dc9a?ixid=M3w5NTU4NjF8MHwxfHNlYXJjaHwxfHxGb3J0JTIwQmVsZ2ljYSUyMFRpZG9yZSUyMGNvbG9uaWFsfGVufDF8MHx8fDE3ODQwNDI4MTJ8MA&ixlib=rb-4.1.0&crop=entropy&cs=tinysrgb&fit=max&fm=jpg&q=80&w=1080","credit":"Matt Dany"},"cardImage":"https://images.unsplash.com/photo-1704797390682-76479a29dc9a?ixid=M3w5NTU4NjF8MHwxfHNlYXJjaHwxfHxGb3J0JTIwQmVsZ2ljYSUyMFRpZG9yZSUyMGNvbG9uaWFsfGVufDF8MHx8fDE3ODQwNDI4MTJ8MA&ixlib=rb-4.1.0&crop=entropy&cs=tinysrgb&fit=max&fm=jpg&q=80&w=1080"}],"top10":[{"rank":1,"name":"Bali","placeId":"bali_denpasar","regionId":"bali","regionName":"Bali","image":{"index":0,"assetPath":"","isLocal":false,"url":"https://images.unsplash.com/photo-1555400038-63f5ba517a47?ixid=M3w5NTU4NjF8MHwxfHNlYXJjaHwxfHxCYWxpJTIwSW5kb25lc2lhfGVufDF8MHx8fDE3ODQwMzQ4MzR8MA&ixlib=rb-4.1.0&crop=entropy&cs=tinysrgb&fit=max&fm=jpg&q=80&w=1080","credit":"Niklas Weiss"},"description":"Bali is Indonesia's most famous island destination, known for its stunning beaches, terraced rice paddies, and vibrant Hindu culture. It attracts millions of visitors annually for its world-class resorts, water sports, temples, and nightlife."},{"rank":2,"name":"Jakarta","placeId":"jakarta_city","regionId":"jakarta","regionName":"Jakarta","image":{"index":0,"assetPath":"","isLocal":false,"url":"https://images.unsplash.com/photo-1555899434-94d1368aa7af?ixid=M3w5NTU4NjF8MHwxfHNlYXJjaHwxfHxKYWthcnRhJTIwSW5kb25lc2lhfGVufDF8MHx8fDE3ODQwMzQ4NTV8MA&ixlib=rb-4.1.0&crop=entropy&cs=tinysrgb&fit=max&fm=jpg&q=80&w=1080","credit":"Eko Herwantoro"},"description":"Jakarta is Indonesia's capital and largest city, serving as the main entry point for international visitors and the country's economic hub. Tourists visit for shopping, dining, museums, and business purposes."},{"rank":3,"name":"Yogyakarta","placeId":"yogyakarta","regionId":"central_java","regionName":"Central Java","image":{"index":0,"assetPath":"","isLocal":false,"url":"https://images.unsplash.com/photo-1631002165376-87fa18968df7?ixid=M3w5NTU4NjF8MHwxfHNlYXJjaHwxfHxZb2d5YWthcnRhJTIwTWFsaW9ib3JvJTIwc3RyZWV0fGVufDF8MHx8fDE3ODM5ODAxOTR8MA&ixlib=rb-4.1.0&crop=entropy&cs=tinysrgb&fit=max&fm=jpg&q=80&w=1080","credit":"Farhan Abas"},"description":"The cultural heart of Java and Indonesia's artistic center, home to traditional batik, puppet shows, and numerous museums and galleries. It serves as the essential base for exploring Central Java's temples, with excellent local food, vibrant street life, and a thriving arts scene."},{"rank":4,"name":"Borobudur Temple","placeId":"borobudur","regionId":"central_java","regionName":"Central Java","image":{"index":0,"assetPath":"","isLocal":false,"url":"https://images.unsplash.com/photo-1631340729644-8b8aad1e9dba?ixid=M3w5NTU4NjF8MHwxfHNlYXJjaHwxfHxCb3JvYnVkdXIlMjB0ZW1wbGUlMjBzdW5yaXNlfGVufDF8MHx8fDE3ODM5ODAxOTJ8MA&ixlib=rb-4.1.0&crop=entropy&cs=tinysrgb&fit=max&fm=jpg&q=80&w=1080","credit":"Manya Krishnaswamy"},"description":"The world's largest Buddhist temple complex, built in the 8th century with over 500 Buddha statues and intricate stone carvings spread across nine levels. It is one of Indonesia's most iconic monuments and a UNESCO World Heritage Site offering profound spiritual and architectural experiences."},{"rank":5,"name":"Lombok Island","placeId":"lombok_island","regionId":"west_nusa_tenggara","regionName":"West Nusa Tenggara","image":{"index":0,"assetPath":"","isLocal":false,"url":"https://images.unsplash.com/photo-1660020214290-800d5775a867?ixid=M3w5NTU4NjF8MHwxfHNlYXJjaHwxfHxMb21ib2slMjBpc2xhbmQlMjBiZWFjaHxlbnwxfDB8fHwxNzg0MDEzNjE5fDA&ixlib=rb-4.1.0&crop=entropy&cs=tinysrgb&fit=max&fm=jpg&q=80&w=1080","credit":"Kilian Karger"},"description":"Lombok is the second-largest island in the Nusa Tenggara archipelago, offering pristine beaches, dramatic volcanic landscapes, and a more laid-back atmosphere than Bali. It's the essential hub for exploring the region with excellent beaches like Kuta and Senggigi, plus access to Mount Rinjani and the Gili Islands."},{"rank":6,"name":"Surabaya","placeId":"surabaya","regionId":"east_java","regionName":"East Java","image":{"index":0,"assetPath":"","isLocal":false,"url":"https://images.unsplash.com/photo-1721413058496-bf42624ccf1c?ixid=M3w5NTU4NjF8MHwxfHNlYXJjaHwxfHxTdXJhYmF5YSUyMGNpdHklMjBza3lsaW5lfGVufDF8MHx8fDE3ODM5ODAyMzd8MA&ixlib=rb-4.1.0&crop=entropy&cs=tinysrgb&fit=max&fm=jpg&q=80&w=1080","credit":"Puji Nugroho"},"description":"East Java's largest city and a major port, Surabaya is a vibrant urban center with a rich revolutionary history and growing modern attractions. It serves as the gateway to the region and offers museums, colonial architecture, and excellent local cuisine."},{"rank":7,"name":"Mount Bromo","placeId":"mount_bromo","regionId":"east_java","regionName":"East Java","image":{"index":0,"assetPath":"","isLocal":false,"url":"https://images.unsplash.com/photo-1588668214407-6ea9a6d8c272?ixid=M3w5NTU4NjF8MHwxfHNlYXJjaHwxfHxNb3VudCUyMEJyb21vJTIwc3VucmlzZXxlbnwxfDB8fHwxNzgzOTgwMjM5fDA&ixlib=rb-4.1.0&crop=entropy&cs=tinysrgb&fit=max&fm=jpg&q=80&w=1080","credit":"Kevin Zhang"},"description":"One of Indonesia's most iconic active volcanoes, Bromo offers dramatic moonlit sunrise hikes across the Sea of Sand with otherworldly crater views. It's the region's most popular natural attraction and a bucket-list experience for adventure travelers."},{"rank":8,"name":"Prambanan Temple","placeId":"prambanan","regionId":"central_java","regionName":"Central Java","image":{"index":0,"assetPath":"","isLocal":false,"url":"https://images.unsplash.com/photo-1765680483070-5e358d2bcc7d?ixid=M3w5NTU4NjF8MHwxfHNlYXJjaHwxfHxQcmFtYmFuYW4lMjB0ZW1wbGUlMjB0b3dlcnN8ZW58MXwwfHx8MTc4Mzk4MDE5Nnww&ixlib=rb-4.1.0&crop=entropy&cs=tinysrgb&fit=max&fm=jpg&q=80&w=1080","credit":"Albertus Gilang Drigantoro Saputro"},"description":"A magnificent 10th-century Hindu temple with three soaring pointed towers rising dramatically from the landscape, representing the trinity of Brahma, Vishnu, and Shiva. Its distinctive silhouette and intricate reliefs make it a UNESCO World Heritage Site and one of Java's most visually striking monuments."},{"rank":9,"name":"Bandung","placeId":"bandung","regionId":"west_java","regionName":"West Java","image":{"index":0,"assetPath":"","isLocal":false,"url":"https://images.unsplash.com/photo-1770006488208-e14a3395c04c?ixid=M3w5NTU4NjF8MHwxfHNlYXJjaHwxfHxCYW5kdW5nJTIwY2l0eSUyMHN0cmVldHN8ZW58MXwwfHx8MTc4Mzk4MDE2MHww&ixlib=rb-4.1.0&crop=entropy&cs=tinysrgb&fit=max&fm=jpg&q=80&w=1080","credit":"luthfian alfajr"},"description":"West Java's capital and largest city, known for its cool mountain climate, vibrant arts scene, and colonial architecture mixed with modern cafes and fashion outlets. It's a cultural hub offering museums, galleries, tea plantations, and serves as a base for exploring surrounding natural attractions."},{"rank":10,"name":"Lake Toba","placeId":"lake_toba","regionId":"north_sumatra","regionName":"North Sumatra","image":{"index":0,"assetPath":"","isLocal":false,"url":"https://images.unsplash.com/photo-1591284915748-bc48608e894d?ixid=M3w5NTU4NjF8MHwxfHNlYXJjaHwxfHxMYWtlJTIwVG9iYSUyMHZvbGNhbmljJTIwbGFrZSUyMFN1bWF0cmF8ZW58MXwwfHx8MTc4Mzk3Mjk5OHww&ixlib=rb-4.1.0&crop=entropy&cs=tinysrgb&fit=max&fm=jpg&q=80&w=1080","credit":"Levi T."},"description":"The world's largest volcanic lake and a UNESCO Global Geopark, offering stunning mountain scenery, cool highland climate, and opportunities for hiking and water activities. The serene landscape and Batak cultural villages make it North Sumatra's most iconic destination."}]}